---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Cigna Global in Italy', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-coverage', text: 'Visa Compliance', level: 2 },
  { id: 'italy-network', text: 'Network Coverage in Italy', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'vs-local-options', text: 'vs Italian Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-its-for', text: 'Who Should Choose Cigna', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Italy', href: '/countries/italy/insurance' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Cigna vs Allianz', href: '/compare/cigna-global-vs-allianz-care' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'italyPrice', header: 'Italy (Age 40)' },
  { key: 'visaCompliant', header: 'Visa Compliant' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Silver', coverage: 'Inpatient + Day-patient', italyPrice: '€140-190/mo', visaCompliant: 'Check' },
  { plan: 'Gold', coverage: 'Silver + Outpatient', italyPrice: '€200-270/mo', visaCompliant: 'Yes' },
  { plan: 'Platinum', coverage: 'Gold + Enhanced', italyPrice: '€280-380/mo', visaCompliant: 'Yes' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Cigna Global Health Insurance in Italy"
  description="Guide to using Cigna Global in Italy. Visa compliance, Italian network coverage, and how it compares to SSN and local options."
  headline="Cigna Global Health Insurance in Italy"
  subheadline="Is Cigna Global the right choice for expats in Italy? Visa coverage, Italian network, and when to keep international insurance."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/italy-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get a Cigna Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Cigna Global in Italy</h2>
  <p>
    Cigna Global serves expats in Italy primarily during the pre-SSN period—covering visa applications and the months before you can enroll in Italy's public healthcare system. It's also valuable for those who travel frequently or want English-speaking support.
  </p>
  <p>
    Italy has excellent public healthcare (SSN), but access requires residency establishment. Cigna bridges this gap and provides worldwide coverage that the Italian system doesn't offer.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">1.5M+</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Providers worldwide</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">24/7</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">English support</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">Pre-SSN</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Immediate coverage</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get an Italy-Specific Quote"
    description="See what Cigna Global costs for expats living in Italy."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna-global"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="visa-coverage">Visa Compliance</h2>
  <p>
    Italian visas (Elective Residence, Digital Nomad, Student) require proof of comprehensive health insurance. Cigna Global Gold and Platinum plans meet these requirements.
  </p>

  <h3>Visa Application Requirements</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Comprehensive coverage:</strong> Inpatient and outpatient required</li>
    <li><strong>Valid in Italy:</strong> Coverage for the full visa duration</li>
    <li><strong>Adequate limits:</strong> Italian consulates expect substantial coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>After SSN Enrollment</h3>
  <p>
    Once you have SSN access (after permesso di soggiorno), you can decide whether to keep Cigna for worldwide coverage and private care access, or rely on the Italian public system.
  </p>

  <h2 id="italy-network">Network Coverage in Italy</h2>
  <p>
    Cigna Global has a strong network in Italy, particularly in major cities with international hospitals.
  </p>

  <h3>Key Network Points</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Rome:</strong> Rome American Hospital, Salvator Mundi International Hospital</li>
    <li><strong>Milan:</strong> Humanitas, San Raffaele Hospital</li>
    <li><strong>Florence:</strong> Meyer Children's Hospital, private clinics</li>
    <li><strong>Reimbursement:</strong> Any licensed Italian provider, submit for reimbursement</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Which Plan for Italy?</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Silver:</strong> Inpatient only—may not meet visa requirements</li>
    <li><strong>Gold:</strong> The practical choice for most expats</li>
    <li><strong>Platinum:</strong> Maximum coverage for those wanting top-tier care</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="vs-local-options">vs Italian Options</h2>

  <h3>Keep Cigna Global If:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>You're in the pre-SSN period</li>
    <li>You travel outside Italy frequently</li>
    <li>English-speaking support is essential</li>
    <li>You might relocate from Italy</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Switch to SSN If:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>You're staying in Italy long-term</li>
    <li>Budget is a concern (SSN is free/low-cost)</li>
    <li>You're comfortable with Italian healthcare</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who Should Choose Cigna in Italy</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Good Fit</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
        <li>New arrivals (pre-SSN period)</li>
        <li>Visa applicants needing coverage</li>
        <li>Expats who travel frequently</li>
        <li>Those wanting English support</li>
        <li>People who might relocate</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Consider Alternatives</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Long-term Italy residents (SSN)</li>
        <li>Budget-conscious expats</li>
        <li>Those comfortable with Italian system</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready for Coverage in Italy?"
    description="Get a personalized Cigna Global quote for your situation."
    buttonText="Get Your Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna-global"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Visa requirements and SSN enrollment rules change. Verify all information with Cigna Global and Italian authorities.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
